article.description: AJ Green had 22 points as Northern Iowa beat Valparaiso 64-53 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Green scores 22 to lead N. Iowa over Valparaiso 64-53
article.linkText: Green scores 22 to lead N. Iowa over Valparaiso 64-53
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- AJ Green had 22 points as Northern Iowa beat Valparaiso 64-53 on Saturday night. Luke McDonnell had 13 points for Northern Iowa (14-15, 9-7 Missouri Valley Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive win. Javon Freeman had 11 points for the Crusaders (14-15, 7-9). Derrik Smits added 10 points and three assists. The Panthers leveled the season series against the Crusaders with the win. Valparaiso defeated Northern Iowa 75-66 on Jan. 19. Northern Iowa plays Loyola of Chicago at home on Wednesday. Valparaiso plays Bradley on the road on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
